LoopVectorization should demote for SIMD
```julia&gt; @btime @avxt $Afloat32 .+= 1.0;
  5.955 μs (0 allocations: 0 bytes)

julia&gt; @btime @avxt $Afloat32 .+= 1f0;
  6.063 μs (0 allocations: 0 bytes)```
Because there is a source/destination vector of type `Float32`, that will trump the scalar `Float64` .

